<b>Description:</b> given a username and a range of posts to look in, this code will automatically quote all posts from the specified player into the reply field.<br>
<br>
<i>Note: this code does not work on Android, iOS, or any other device without a javascript web console.</i><br>
<br>
<span class="cmty-hide-heading faux-link" onclick="AoPS.Community.Utils.clickHide($(this));" href="#">Instructions</span><div class="cmty-hide-content" style="display:none"><b>Step 1: Load the posts you want to ISO.</b><br>
The code cannot retrieve a player’s posts if you do not have them currently loaded in your browser, so you must scroll down (or up) through the thread to load the posts you want in your ISO. AoPS periodically refuses to load posts when scrolling up; if this happens, “bounce” the thread by scrolling down for a bit before scrolling back up.<br>
<b>Step 2: Open your browser’s console. </b><br>
For Chrome, the shortcut is <b>Control + Shift + J</b> (Windows, Linux, Chrome OS) or <b>Command + Option + J</b> (macOS). For Safari, first enable Developer Menu by going to Safari Menu &gt; Preferences &gt; Advanced tab and checking “Show Develop menu in menu bar,” then use the shortcut <b>Command + Option + C</b>. For Firefox, the shortcut is <b>Control + Shift + K</b> (Windows, Linux) or <b>Command + Option + K</b> (macOS). For Microsoft Edge, the shortcut is <b>Control + Shift + J</b>.<br>
<b>Step 3: Copy/paste the code into the console and hit Enter.</b><br>
Once you do so, the code will prompt you in a popup, and you will not be able to access the tab you are running the code on. Do not switch to another tab in the same window, or the code will not work.<br>
<b>Step 4: Enter the username of the player you are ISOing. </b><br>
This is case-sensitive; capitalize and spell the username correctly.<br>
<b>Step 5: Enter the first post of your ISO range.</b><br>
If you are doing a full ISO, you can use 1 or 0. If you are doing a partial ISO, enter the post number from which you want the code to search for a player’s posts.<br>
<b>Step 6: Enter the last post of your ISO range.</b><br>
If you are doing a full ISO, enter any number larger than the thread postcount; 10000 works. If you are doing a partial ISO, enter the post number to which you want the code to search for a player’s posts. Please note that posts that are within the range you have specified, but that have not been loaded in your browser, will not be included by the code in the ISO.<br>
<br>
Once you have done so, the reply field will open, with all the relevant posts quoted in it.</div><br>
<br>
